At Avyakta, we are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring a transparent user experience. This Cookie Policy explains how and why cookies are used on our platform.

What Are Cookies?

Cookies are small text files stored on your device when you visit a website. They help us remember your preferences, improve site performance, and keep your experience safe and smooth.

Types of Cookies We Use

  • 1. Essential Cookies
    These are required for the website to function properly. They enable core features like secure login, form submission, and language switching.
  • 2. Functional Cookies
    These remember your choices (like language preference or display settings) to enhance your experience.
  • 3. Analytics Cookies
    We use anonymous analytics (e.g., Google Analytics or internal tools) to understand how our users interact with our site, so we can make it better.
  • 4. Security Cookies
    Used to detect and prevent fraudulent activities and keep your data safe during form submissions and chat sessions.

We Do Not:

  • Track you for advertising purposes.
  • Sell or share your personal data.
  • Allow third-party ads on our website.

How Can You Control Cookies?

You can manage or disable cookies through your browser settings at any time. Please note that disabling certain cookies may affect your experience on our site.

üëâ Common Options:
  • Chrome: Settings > Privacy > Cookies
  • Firefox: Options > Privacy & Security
  • Safari: Preferences > Privacy

Questions?

For any concerns regarding your privacy or cookie usage, please email us at:
privacy@avyakta.org

Respecting Your Dignity
Because our mission deals with sensitive human matters, we treat all your data with care, responsibility, and confidentiality.
